<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[192,1441,1763,1883]" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,1763,1787]" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2017" box="[331,508,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sandy">
<emphasis box="[331,508,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">Prodilis sandy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2017" box="[780,878,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kristi">
<emphasis box="[780,798,1764,1787]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[813,878,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">kristi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by more intensely blue elytral surface, lateral pronotal margin more narrowly pale, and basal prosternal margin not medially emarginate. This species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2017" box="[299,397,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Prodilis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kristi">
<emphasis box="[299,317,1828,1851]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[332,397,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="83">kristi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may represent the same species with differences noted here only intraspecific variations.
</paragraph>
